&lt;p&gt;At Lightspeed Systems, we&#39;re on a mission to help schools create safer, more effective digital learning environments. Trusted by thousands of schools worldwide, our solutions help education leaders manage technology, protect students, and improve learning outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we continue to grow across the UK, we&#39;re looking for a motivated Account Executive to join our sales team and help introduce our solutions to new schools and multi-academy trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive, you&#39;ll be responsible for generating new business opportunities, managing sales cycles, and building relationships with education leaders across your territory. You&#39;ll work closely with Marketing, Customer Success, and Sales leadership to identify customer needs and demonstrate how Lightspeed&#39;s solutions can help schools achieve their goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone with early sales experience who enjoys prospecting, building relationships, and developing a consultative sales approach in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About The Role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate new business opportunities through outbound prospecting, inbound lead follow-up, and networking activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the sales process from initial outreach through proposal, negotiation, and close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct discovery conversations to understand customer challenges, priorities, and technology initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver engaging product demonstrations and presentations to school and trust stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare proposals, quotations, and sales documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain regular communication with prospects and customers throughout the buying process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support customer renewal and expansion conversations when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain an accurate pipeline within Salesforce CRM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Marketing on campaigns, events, webinars, and lead-generation initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend industry conferences, exhibitions, and customer events as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay informed on education technology trends and market developments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About You&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in sales, business development, account management, or a customer-facing commercial role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and relationship-building skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable engaging customers via phone, email, video meetings, and in-person presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with strong attention to detail and follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated with a desire to build a successful career in sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Office and CRM systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in SaaS, technology, or EdTech environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the UK education sector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Salesforce or similar CRM platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree-level education or equivalent professional experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
