&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing and executing comprehensive test plans and strategies with a focus on teacher and student workflows across Chrome, web, and real-time messaging surfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participating in Agile Scrum ceremonies, story definitions, and sprint planning alongside product and engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing test scenarios from Epics, User Stories, and acceptance criteria, paying particular attention to multi-device, multi-student edge cases that mirror real classroom conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying, reproducing, and documenting defects with exceptional precision and detail; collaborating with developers and stakeholders for timely resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing UAT environments, triaging issues, and ensuring optimal test coverage across supported platforms (ChromeOS, Windows, Mac) and varying network configurations typical of school environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and updating the defect backlog using JIRA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating UAT test efforts with internal teams, customers, and external partners, including gathering feedback from educators and district IT administrators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Producing test metrics and delivering detailed reports to drive improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting production releases and managing the escalation process during support events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validating real-time features such as screen monitoring, screen sharing, device lock, link pushing, and messaging to ensure reliability under realistic classroom-scale conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;NOTE:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a hybrid position and several days each week will be required onsite at our Austin, Texas headquarters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sponsorship is not available for this position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
